      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI below 5% on finest mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study performed; GCI computed via Richardson extrapolation. GCI on hemolysis index QoI is 8.3% on the finest mesh, exceeding the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 does not meet required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicate all five COU flow-speed operating points with documented uncertainty in flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid temperature.",
      "rationale": "Four of five COU operating points were replicated in bench testing. The fifth high-speed point (6000 RPM, 6 L/min) was not tested due to equipment limitations. Uncertainty budgets are documented for the four tested points. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E_rel) computed for hemolysis index at all COU operating points; simulation results within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "Relative error on hemolysis index ranges from 18% to 47% across the four tested operating points, substantially outside combined uncertainty bands. The model systematically underpredicts hemolysis at high shear-stress conditions. Achieved level 2 is far below required level 5 for Class III absolute prediction."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs are the same absolute hemolysis index values required by the COU; no surrogate or proxy quantities used.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) which is the COU QoI. However, NIH was computed from bulk outlet measurements rather than spatially resolved predictions, introducing aggregation uncertainty not captured in the comparison. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same pump geometry and blood analog fluid as the COU; operating envelope fully covered.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which matches the COU device geometry. However, a glycerol-water blood analog was used rather than porcine blood, introducing fluid property discrepancies for viscosity and red blood cell fragility. Operating envelope coverage is partial. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria documented; residuals and QoI monitors confirm solver convergence to within tolerance for all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitoring was not systematically documented for all five operating points. Residual logs were retained for only two runs. This factor is flagged as a MRL 5 epistemic gap; achieved level 1 reflects absence of documented evidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing scripts performed by a qualified analyst not involved in the original simulation.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. Boundary condition specification and post-processing scripts were authored and applied by the same analyst without peer review. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal justification of turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model selection; sensitivity analysis across plausible model form alternatives documented.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected without documented comparison to alternative turbulence closures. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model was applied without sensitivity analysis against alternative damage models (e.g., Arora, Zhang). Model form uncertainty is the dominant epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary condition values traceable to measurements with documented uncertainty; Monte Carlo propagation covers all influential inputs.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed covering flow rate and rotational speed uncertainty. Blood viscosity, hematocrit, and hemolysis model coefficients (C, alpha, beta) were treated as fixed nominal values without uncertainty propagation, despite being identified as influential parameters in literature. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood analog fluid characterized per ASTM standards; hematocrit and osmotic fragility documented for each test run; inter-batch variability assessed.",
      "rationale": "Fluid characterization records for the glycerol-water blood analog are incomplete. Hematocrit equivalence was not established and inter-batch variability was not assessed across the experimental campaign. Flagged as epistemic gap; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency mapping between validation experiment inputs and COU inputs documented; any deviations quantified and their impact on QoI assessed.",
      "rationale": "No formal equivalency mapping was produced between the bench validation experiment inputs and the COU inputs. Fluid property differences (glycerol-water vs. blood), temperature deviations, and inlet velocity profile differences were acknowledged in the report but not quantified for their impact on the hemolysis QoI. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
