    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The 13-factor credibility assessment for COU2 (VAD hemolysis, MRL 5) has been completed and all factor evaluations documented. Although achieved levels fall below required levels across all assessed factors and six factors carry epistemic-gap flags, the assessment package itself is accepted as a complete and valid credibility evidence record for regulatory submission purposes. The decision reflects acceptance of the assessment process and documentation, not acceptance of the model for its intended use. Remediation plan for the seven identified gaps (model form uncertainty, use error review, solver convergence logging, test sample characterization, input equivalency mapping, fluid analog fidelity, and output comparison improvement) is required prior to re-assessment at MRL 5.",
